If I understood correctly your problem, you&#39;re trying to get a `List` containing all the possible combinations of the input map, where each combination (or option) contains every key paired with only one of the values of their corresponding list.

Personally, I would tackle this problem by using recursion where each recursive step works on a specific key. On each recursive call, the list of values of the current key is traversed and the `i-th` value is added to a temporary `Map` to create a possible option. Once a stack of recursive calls ends, it means that there are no further keys to visit and that an option has been built. 

Basically, the whole core lies within the for loop, where each key continues to populate an option from the previous key&#39;s `i-th` value.

```
public static void getCombinations(Map&lt;String, List&lt;String&gt;&gt; mapInput, List&lt;Map&lt;String, String&gt;&gt; listRes) {
    getCombinationsHelper(mapInput, listRes, new HashMap&lt;&gt;(), new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(mapInput.keySet()), 0);
}

private static void getCombinationsHelper(Map&lt;String, List&lt;String&gt;&gt; mapInput, List&lt;Map&lt;String, String&gt;&gt; listRes, Map&lt;String, String&gt; mapOption, List&lt;String&gt; keys, int keyIndex) {
    //Base case where there are no further keys, so the option is complete and it can be added to the resulting list
    if (keyIndex == keys.size()) {
        listRes.add(new HashMap&lt;&gt;(mapOption));
        return;
    }

    //Traversing the key&#39;s values
    List&lt;String&gt; value = mapInput.get(keys.get(keyIndex));
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; value.size(); i++) {
        //Adding the key&#39;s i-th value into the option
        mapOption.put(keys.get(keyIndex), value.get(i));

        //Moving to the next key to populate the option
        getCombinationsHelper(mapInput, listRes, mapOption, keys, keyIndex + 1);

        //Removing the key&#39;s i-th value to create another combination with the next value
        mapOption.remove(keys.get(keyIndex));
    }
}

public static void main(String[] args) {
    Map&lt;String, List&lt;String&gt;&gt; mapValues = Map.of(
            &quot;delivery&quot;, List.of(&quot;food&quot;, &quot;drink&quot;),
            &quot;service&quot;, List.of(&quot;taxi&quot;, &quot;motor-bike&quot;),
            &quot;application&quot;, List.of(&quot;mobile-device&quot;)
    );

    List&lt;Map&lt;String, String&gt;&gt; listCombinations = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
    getCombinations(mapValues, listCombinations);

    for (Map&lt;String, String&gt; map : listCombinations) {
        System.out.println(map);
    }
}
