To keep the loose coupling here, you can use the [Adapter](https://refactoring.guru/design-patterns/adapter) design pattern which suits very well on enriching/extracting data to make it compatible to a new interface.

Also, your `EnrichedTestProjectRequest` should extend `TestProjectRequest`, because those classes are linked, and in your interface you can have:

```java
public interface TestProjectService {
  void process(TestProjectRequest  request);
}
```
This way you make the contract more restrictive, requesting only the data you need and nothing more. This is just an example, you should update it according to your needs.

