The &#39;audience&#39; and the &#39;subject&#39; are inside the body of the JWT, they are called &#39;aud&#39; and &#39;sub&#39; and will have the following structure:

```
{
    &quot;alg&quot;: &quot;ES256&quot;,
    &quot;kid&quot;: &quot;ABC123DEFG&quot;
}
{
    &quot;iss&quot;: &quot;DEF123GHIJ&quot;,
    &quot;iat&quot;: 1437179036,
    &quot;exp&quot;: 1493298100,
    &quot;aud&quot;: &quot;https://appleid.apple.com&quot;,
    &quot;sub&quot;: &quot;com.mytest.app&quot;
}
```

Where the fields you are looking for are:
```    
&quot;aud&quot;: &quot;https://appleid.apple.com&quot;,
&quot;sub&quot;: &quot;com.mytest.app&quot;
```

You can check [this link](https://developer.apple.com/documentation/sign_in_with_apple/generate_and_validate_tokens) for more information.

